cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the design of a distributed dynamic spectrum protocol for ad-hoc device-to-device communication in cellular networks. This involves managing interference and utilizing spectrum resources more efficiently. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves channel gain estimates and transmission power control, which are related to information theory and communication theory, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses interference management, which is a key aspect of security in wireless networks, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category. The paper also involves the design of a distributed protocol, which is related to control systems and automation, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses power savings, which is related to multimedia systems and applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
